1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,878
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,962 --> 00:00:08,550
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,633 --> 00:00:12,846
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

4
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:16,725
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i>
<i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

5
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:17,976
[audience exclaims]

6
00:00:18,059 --> 00:00:19,894
[Janine] <i>Even if she's joined</i>
<i>by her fake father,</i>

7
00:00:19,978 --> 00:00:21,438
<i>the people are still laughing at her.</i>

8
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:23,440
- [audience exclaims]
- [Janine cackles]

9
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,191
[audience] Ibyang! Ibyang!

10
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:28,028
It feels like my performance
turned out better.

11
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:31,031
<i>Thank you, Master. You're the best!</i>

12
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:35,326
<i>We both know you're the one</i>
<i>who put blue paint on my face.</i>

13
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:37,203
Don't accuse me!

14
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:38,872
[Janine shrieks]

15
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:41,082
Ibyang, what are you doing to Janine?!

16
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:43,209
She should be the one apologizing to me!

17
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,711
She's a bad kid!

18
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:45,837
Stop it!

19
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,338
[Ibyang] <i>I grew up in an orphanage.</i>

20
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:52,093
<i>Master Atoy and Sis Tonet</i>
<i>stand as my parents.</i>

21
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:53,762
And that's probably

22
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:57,057
the greatest gift they've given me.

23
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,975
[cheering]

24
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,227
[sobs] Our child is making me cry.

25
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:04,939
[principal, in English] <i>Our 2026</i>
<i>Little Miss Primary School,</i>

26
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:07,442
<i>Ms. Janine Ranoy!</i>

27
00:01:07,525 --> 00:01:10,570
[Ibyang] It's okay with me
that I didn't win

28
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:13,990
because the whole experience was so fun!

29
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:14,908
[Atoy] <i>So? Did you enjoy?</i>

30
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:19,079
It feels like this is
the best day of my life!

31
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:22,248
Can you be my official Daddy Atoy?

32
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:24,000
PREVIOUSLY

33
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,335
I'd love that.

34
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:38,223
[music fades]

35
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:45,939
Dear…

36
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:49,400
So, where do you want
to display your crown?

37
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:51,319
It's beautiful.

38
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:53,363
Just keep it in your room.

39
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:54,948
It doesn't mean anything to me anyway.

40
00:01:55,031 --> 00:01:55,990
Huh?

41
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:59,828
How could you say that!

42
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:02,163
[sighs] Even though I won,

43
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:05,208
everyone still likes Ibyang more!

44
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:09,379
Janine, you did well.

45
00:02:10,046 --> 00:02:13,800
It's just that she really had
a lot of people with her.

46
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:15,844
Did you notice?

47
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:18,221
It was like the whole barangay was there.

48
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:20,765
So, why didn't you bring more friends?

49
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:24,394
[somber music playing]

50
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:27,772
Um, because, dear. Well, um…

51
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,442
Here's what we'll do.

52
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,820
To end this,

53
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:38,449
I think I need to transfer you
to a new school.

54
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:41,077
I'll talk to your teacher tomorrow. Okay?

55
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:42,704
Right away?

56
00:02:42,787 --> 00:02:44,581
I thought we'll do it next year?

57
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,791
I don't want to transfer schools.

58
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:51,212
Janine, this fight between you
and Ibyang isn't healthy anymore.

59
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:53,673
That's why I want to transfer you
as soon as possible.

60
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:55,049
You're so stubborn, Mommy!

61
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:56,259
I don't want to!

62
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:58,261
My friends are there!

63
00:02:58,344 --> 00:03:00,471
Don't talk to me like that.

64
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:02,056
[in English] I'm still your mother!

65
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:04,183
[unsettling music playing]

66
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:05,810
I'm tired. I'm going to sleep.

67
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:15,737
[suave theme music playing]

68
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:46,184
Oh, ma'am!

69
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:47,769
Why are you still awake?

70
00:03:51,147 --> 00:03:55,610
Nanny, how many kids
do you have in the province?

71
00:03:58,321 --> 00:03:59,989
I have six children.

72
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,449
Two are here in Manila.

73
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:02,992
Why do you ask?

74
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:08,873
Because this is all new to me.

75
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,751
Being a mother.

76
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:18,007
But why… why do I feel this way
about my own child?

77
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:19,926
What do you mean?

78
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:24,264
[somber music playing]

79
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:27,016
I feel so distant from her.

80
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:30,478
Like she didn't come from me.

81
00:04:32,146 --> 00:04:35,775
Sometimes she just annoys me.

82
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,195
It's exhausting.

83
00:04:40,822 --> 00:04:45,118
Ma'am, it's normal to feel annoyed
and tired with our children.

84
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:47,704
We, parents, are only human.

85
00:04:48,204 --> 00:04:51,332
And Ma'am Janine grew up
with other people,

86
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:56,129
so she picked up habits
that aren't like yours.

87
00:04:57,213 --> 00:04:58,756
I know that.

88
00:05:00,216 --> 00:05:03,177
But she's so different from…

89
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:05,972
[music fades]

90
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:09,434
[maid] Excuse me, ma'am.

91
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:14,772
I hate to say it, Audrey, but…

92
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:17,567
you should be the one adjusting
to your own child.

93
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:19,652
[in English] You're supposed
to love them, accept them,

94
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:21,946
and mold them in the right direction.

95
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:24,490
What you're feeling about
Janine isn't helping.

96
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:30,496
I wouldn't feel this way about Janine
if you hadn't separated me from my child.

97
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:32,957
That's still your issue?

98
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,585
[in English] You can't keep blaming
everything on the past.

99
00:05:35,668 --> 00:05:37,336
[in English] Oh my God, Audrey!

100
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:39,297
She's still your daughter, no matter what!

101
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:43,468
[sinister music playing]

102
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:01,569
[in English] Wow! I knew it!

103
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,946
- Can I taste it, Aunt?
- Ah, w-w-wait!

104
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:04,989
It's still hot!

105
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:06,657
[in English] Let it cool down first.

106
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:09,869
[in English] Um, so what's up with you?

107
00:06:09,952 --> 00:06:13,498
You know, Janine won the school pageant.

108
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:15,666
Yes, I heard. Mommy told me.

109
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:16,667
[in English] It's nice to hear.

110
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:18,628
- Amazing.
- I wish you were there.

111
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:22,381
[in English] Um, what's been
up with you lately?

112
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:25,218
I'm excited.

113
00:06:25,301 --> 00:06:27,553
At the same time, I feel nervous.

114
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:29,097
I have an upcoming date.

115
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:31,682
[in English] Ah, wow!

116
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,518
[in English] That's great news.

117
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:34,894
[in English] Care to share?

118
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,855
[in English] Hmm, next time, Auntie.

119
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:39,482
When I actually have something
to share with you.

120
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,360
Okay.

121
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:49,033
[pensive music playing]

122
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,496
- Delicious!
- [Audrey] Oh!

123
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:55,039
This is my new favorite.

124
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,001
[in English] Are you okay, Auntie?

125
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:01,754
Huh?

126
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:02,922
Are you okay?

127
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,298
[in English] Yes. Of course, I'm fine.

128
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,217
It's just that…

129
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:10,847
Janine often fights
with someone at school.

130
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:14,392
[in English] Her name is Ibyang.

131
00:07:15,017 --> 00:07:16,936
Is this the same girl
she fought with at the theme park?

132
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,354
[in English] Yes.

133
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:22,358
[in English] You know, I don't want
to sound like a bad mother.

134
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,277
[in English] But I can't help but think…

135
00:07:25,069 --> 00:07:29,907
What if Janine really is the one
at fault in her quarrels with Ibyang?

136
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:33,161
Like at the pageant, they were fighting!

137
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:36,873
Of course, I'll side
with my daughter, Janine.

138
00:07:37,748 --> 00:07:40,126
But I feel guilty because…

139
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:44,088
I raised my voice at Ibyang.

140
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:46,132
[gentle music playing]

141
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:48,009
I don't know what to do anymore.

142
00:07:49,093 --> 00:07:50,803
It's simple, Auntie.

143
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:55,391
If you think you were out of line,
then make it up to her.

144
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:57,935
I'm sure she'll forgive you.

145
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,736
[Cita] Oh, didn't I tell you, Atoy?

146
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:09,655
Your fatherly instinct
for Ibyang is natural.

147
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:12,575
She told me she already calls you "Tatoy".

148
00:08:14,118 --> 00:08:17,205
So why don't you make it official?

149
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:24,545
- [in English] Official?
- Hmm.

150
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:26,714
You mean, to adopt her?

151
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:31,886
Yes. Didn't you say your search
for her parents was a dead end?

152
00:08:31,969 --> 00:08:34,430
[mellow music playing]

153
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,348
Well…

154
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,352
Yes. 'Nang,

155
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:41,187
I really thought about that.

156
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,980
Oh? What's the problem?

157
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:45,816
But of course…

158
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:48,277
My work.

159
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:52,823
If I commit to that,
I can't just neglect her.

160
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:55,117
I'd have to dedicate my time

161
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:57,870
to raising her properly.
That wouldn't be possible.

162
00:08:57,954 --> 00:09:01,165
But you did give her time
during the pageant, didn't you?

163
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,376
You even stayed up late making her gown.

164
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:05,169
[Cita] Hmm.

165
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:07,338
Just think about it, Atoy, but…

166
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:09,340
it's good you're considering it.

167
00:09:09,423 --> 00:09:10,675
My concern is…

168
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:13,803
This is a commitment. Priorities.

169
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:15,054
And I know you.

170
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:17,139
If you really want to make it happen,

171
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,141
you can!

172
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:21,102
[chuckles softly]

173
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:25,731
[light music playing]

174
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:26,774
[muffled chattering in the distance]

175
00:09:26,857 --> 00:09:28,067
Dear, um…

176
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:29,652
[girl twitter]

177
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:31,362
[in English] I'm sorry about last night.

178
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,698
If you don't want to transfer schools,

179
00:09:35,032 --> 00:09:35,950
that's fine with me.

180
00:09:37,451 --> 00:09:41,038
I just don't want you
always fighting with Ibyang.

181
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:44,292
I'll just ignore her.

182
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:46,335
That's better, dear.

183
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:49,714
All right then. Have a great day.

184
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:51,757
[in English] I love you.

185
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:53,384
[in English] Okay.

186
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:57,555
Okay, Mom?

187
00:09:57,638 --> 00:09:59,348
[sighs]

188
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:00,641
Okay, Mom.

189
00:10:01,892 --> 00:10:02,893
[Audrey chuckles softly]

190
00:10:04,228 --> 00:10:06,105
[in English] Goodbye, dear.
I'll see you later.

191
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:13,696
[muffled chattering in the distance]

192
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:17,283
[sneaky music playing]

193
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:19,410
[Atoy] What happened to your cheek?

194
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:22,413
- Huh?
- Ah, nothing. Just scratched it.

195
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:25,166
Hey, listen to me.

196
00:10:25,249 --> 00:10:27,043
If ever I'm late picking you up,

197
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:30,880
make sure you never go
with anyone else, all right?

198
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:33,758
You will only go with me. Wait for me.

199
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:36,469
Okay.

200
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:40,097
- All right.
- Tatoy, I love you!

201
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:42,808
Hmm, love you. Love you.

202
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:47,730
All right. Okay now.

203
00:10:48,397 --> 00:10:49,523
All right.

204
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:51,233
Psst! Don't be stubborn, okay?

205
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,485
Yes.

206
00:10:52,568 --> 00:10:55,154
[muffled chattering in the distance]

207
00:10:58,199 --> 00:10:59,450
Ibyang!

208
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:04,163
[somber music playing]

209
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:05,539
Uh, s-sorry.

210
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:07,041
Did I startle you?

211
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,460
Not really.

212
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:11,170
I just wanted…

213
00:11:11,879 --> 00:11:13,923
to apologize to you.

214
00:11:14,882 --> 00:11:18,052
Because I raised my voice
at you during the pageant.

215
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:20,721
You didn't deserve that.

216
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:22,431
It's okay.

217
00:11:23,974 --> 00:11:25,559
I'm sorry too

218
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:27,937
if I pushed your child.

219
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:33,275
I have a surprise for you.

220
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,237
[Audrey] Hmm, hmm.

221
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,988
Your favorite!

222
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:38,989
Are you serious?

223
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:43,494
It's part of my apology to you.

224
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:45,329
[in English] I'm sorry.

225
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:47,706
[light feel-good music playing]

226
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,583
Thank you!

227
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:55,631
But I don't have porridge to give you.

228
00:11:55,714 --> 00:11:57,675
Don't worry. It's fine.

229
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:01,637
I just hope…

230
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:06,475
you and Janine get along.

231
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:09,145
That's my only wish.

232
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:12,731
That's what I want too.

233
00:12:16,735 --> 00:12:17,653
All right then!

234
00:12:17,736 --> 00:12:18,737
You might be late!

235
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,948
Thank you again!

236
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,659
[in English] Bye!

237
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:25,202
[in English] Bye-bye!

238
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:31,959
[chuckles softly]

239
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:35,004
[Janine] Take a look at this.

240
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:37,256
Mommy baked this for me.

241
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:40,217
We have a big oven at home.

242
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:42,470
It must be expensive. It's huge!

243
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:44,388
[in English] Wow!

244
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:46,765
Looks delicious. Can I have some?

245
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,851
No!

246
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:51,103
Mommy made this for me,
and you're taking one?

247
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,521
So selfish.

248
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:56,692
So, are you guys coming later?

249
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:59,361
- We're swimming at our mansion.
- Of course.

250
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,906
We're excited.

251
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:08,579
Mabel, if you want some,
I won't share, okay?

252
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:11,332
Huh? I have some too. Look.

253
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:13,626
[suspicious music playing]

254
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:15,336
Huh?

255
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:16,962
Where did you get that?

256
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:21,967
- Did you take that from my bag?
- No, Janine.

257
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:24,261
Ibyang gave this to me.

258
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:26,430
It looks just like your packed food.

259
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:28,140
What?!

260
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,892
[tense music playing]

261
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:39,693
Ibyang!

262
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:42,863
Where did you get those cookies, huh?

263
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:44,782
Why?

264
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:47,409
Your mommy gave them to me.

265
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:49,370
Do you want some?

266
00:13:49,453 --> 00:13:50,955
What do you mean "want"?

267
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:52,498
You shouldn't even have that.

268
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:54,667
Why?

269
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:57,962
Before you even met your mommy,

270
00:13:58,045 --> 00:14:00,089
we already knew each other.

271
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:03,384
And she made me taste these first.

272
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:07,137
I can give you some if you want. Here.

273
00:14:08,138 --> 00:14:09,306
No!

274
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:12,101
[intense music playing]

275
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,520
Hey-- [gasps]

276
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,275
You're wasting food!

277
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:32,746
Ame.

278
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:33,747
[Ame] Hmm?

279
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,166
Can I ask you something?

280
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:39,587
Of course. I can never say no to you!

281
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,463
[smirks] No!

282
00:14:42,923 --> 00:14:46,677
Do you know or are you familiar
with the process of…

283
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:49,680
adoption?

284
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,640
For whom?

285
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,434
[somber music playing]

286
00:14:53,517 --> 00:14:54,602
For you!

287
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:58,772
Of course not. Of course it's not for you!

288
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:01,066
For… you know who!

289
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,526
[gasps]

290
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,863
Really? You're planning to adopt her?

291
00:15:05,946 --> 00:15:07,448
Well…

292
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:08,866
- [inhales]
- [sentimental music playing]

293
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:11,243
Shh. Don't tell anyone yet.

294
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:12,661
Don't say it to anyone.

295
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,413
Hmm, okay, okay. It's a secret.

296
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:16,206
- It's a secret. Mmm-mmm.
- Secret?

297
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,584
Oh, she'll be so happy!

298
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:42,149
[in English] Welcome to our home, girls!

299
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,069
[Janine] See? I told you!

300
00:15:45,152 --> 00:15:46,946
It's a mansion!

301
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,368
There's the pool.

302
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:53,702
Go ahead.

303
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:55,746
Nanny, accompany them. Please.

304
00:15:55,829 --> 00:15:57,790
Okay, Auntie. Thank you.

305
00:15:57,873 --> 00:15:59,583
We'll go ahead, Janine.

306
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:05,297
Janine.

307
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:10,344
Is something wrong?

308
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:13,555
You've been quiet.

309
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:17,142
I thought you'd enjoy swimming
with your friends.

310
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:18,185
[unsettling music playing]

311
00:16:18,268 --> 00:16:20,020
How can I be happy?

312
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:23,148
You also gave Ibyang
the same cookies you gave me.

313
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:25,776
Oh, there's nothing wrong with that, dear.

314
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:27,987
I only did it as a peace offering.

315
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:31,240
- Because I want you two to get along.
- There's no way.

316
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:34,034
I don't want to be friends with her.

317
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:36,078
I already have friends, right?

318
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:38,497
And I don't want you to be friends
with Ibyang either,

319
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:40,708
because I'm your daughter, Mommy!

320
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,841
[in English] Yes, sir.
I can go to you, sir.

321
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:51,510
[in English] Okay.

322
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:56,140
Atoy, can I borrow some money
for my commute?

323
00:16:56,223 --> 00:16:58,642
I just want to have Ibyang checked up.

324
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:00,936
Oh, why? What happened to her?

325
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:04,148
Well, she got rashes on her face.

326
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:06,316
Maybe because of the poster paint.

327
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,193
[pensive music playing]

328
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:09,737
So that's why her face is red.

329
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,780
Oh, that Ibyang.
Why didn't she say anything?

330
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:14,491
Well, you know that child.

331
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:17,453
If you don't push her, she won't speak.

332
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:20,539
All right, I'll go with you.

333
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,960
Oh, no need.
Ibyang's already troubled you enough.

334
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,713
And I heard you have work to do.

335
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:30,257
So what? I can cancel that.

336
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:33,927
Don't. Go to your work.

337
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:35,888
I'll take care of Ibyang.

338
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:39,308
It's not that serious.
I just want to be sure.

339
00:17:40,976 --> 00:17:42,019
All right then.

340
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:48,650
Here.

341
00:17:49,651 --> 00:17:50,611
For your expenses.

342
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:51,945
Thank you.

343
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:54,156
That Ibyang is really annoying.

344
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:57,159
I feel like putting blue paint
on her face again.

345
00:17:57,868 --> 00:17:59,328
She's such a pest!

346
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:01,580
Even meddling with my mommy.

347
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:03,082
Hey, don't!

348
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,793
She was already humiliated at the pageant.

349
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:07,836
Well, that's just right.

350
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:13,717
Come on, help me think
of what we can do to her next.

351
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:15,469
Janine.

352
00:18:15,552 --> 00:18:17,513
[dramatic sting]

353
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,723
So, it's true what Ibyang said?

354
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:23,352
That you're the one behind
the blue paint on her face?

355
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:28,565
[tense music playing]

356
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:29,858
Mommy…

357
00:18:29,942 --> 00:18:32,236
- You heard it wrong--
- [in English] I heard you, Janine!

358
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:34,738
Don't lie to me!

359
00:18:35,239 --> 00:18:37,533
I defended you!

360
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:40,035
And it turns out you're the one at fault?!

361
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:42,913
[pensive music playing]

362
00:18:42,996 --> 00:18:43,956
Janine.

363
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:47,167
Janine, where are you going? Let's talk!

364
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:48,669
What?

365
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:50,587
You're going to scold me?

366
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:53,465
You're really siding with that Ibyang?

367
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,553
Child, I'm not siding with anyone!

368
00:18:57,636 --> 00:19:00,139
But I know what's right and wrong!

369
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:02,391
And what you did was wrong!

370
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:04,143
It wasn't wrong.

371
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:06,854
That Ibyang is such a show-off.

372
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:09,106
So, she deserved it.

373
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:11,191
[tense music playing]

374
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:18,198
Mmm.

375
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:21,368
Good thing you're free today.

376
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:25,414
I'm not used to you refusing a job order.

377
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:26,790
Sorry, sir.

378
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:30,878
I really just needed to attend
Ibyang's school event.

379
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:34,965
That's good, that you have
another life aside from this.

380
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:36,508
[in English] Anyway…

381
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:38,886
let's get to the mission.

382
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:40,095
[in English] Yes, sir.

383
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:44,349
A Mrs. Santos came to me.

384
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:50,814
She's risking half her life savings

385
00:19:52,691 --> 00:19:57,154
just to find and send this man to jail.

386
00:19:58,197 --> 00:19:59,448
Aldrin Galang.

387
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:04,453
Mrs. Santos's husband met
with Aldrin Galang.

388
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:08,457
He was supposed to be
the buyer of their car.

389
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,375
But he never came back.

390
00:20:11,835 --> 00:20:17,799
After one week, her husband
was found with his head bound,

391
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:20,177
his body burned.

392
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:22,763
Dead.

393
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:25,724
That Aldrin Galang is the prime suspect.

394
00:20:26,516 --> 00:20:28,560
It's been months,

395
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:32,981
but the police still haven't caught him.

396
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:35,317
Based on my intel,

397
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:39,279
he's been collecting from vendors

398
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:42,282
at Road 23, Barangay Macario.

399
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:43,909
Barangay Macario.

400
00:20:43,992 --> 00:20:45,702
[suspicious music playing]

401
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:46,954
I know where that is.

402
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:48,789
[in English] Good.

403
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:51,625
So, Atoy?

404
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:54,920
Shall we help Mrs. Santos?

405
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:55,963
[in English] Yes, sir.

406
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,173
I'll take care of it.

407
00:20:58,257 --> 00:20:59,174
I'll start now.

408
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:00,968
Thank you, Atoy.

409
00:21:01,051 --> 00:21:03,762
Maintain high vigilance on the target.

410
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:09,726
Very hostile, possibly connected
to the syndicate.

411
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:12,271
[in English] Watch your back.

412
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:16,149
Copy, sir. I'll handle it.

413
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:18,193
[rock music playing]

414
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:19,528
[Mercado sighs]

415
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:21,822
- [Audrey] Janine?
- [girl] Yummy.

416
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:23,365
- Janine?
- [girl] Mmm.

417
00:21:24,366 --> 00:21:26,660
Kids, did you see Janine?

418
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:29,705
[girl] We've been looking
for her for a while.

419
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:31,081
Audrey.

420
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:31,957
[gasps]

421
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:32,916
[in English] What's going on?

422
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,211
Dad, I've been looking
for Janine all over.

423
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:39,381
I even asked security to look for her.
But I-I don't know where she is!

424
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:40,966
What really happened?

425
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:45,137
I scolded her earlier,
then she walked out.

426
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:46,638
Now I can't find her.

427
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:47,889
[door lock clicks]

428
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:49,141
[maid] Ma'am Audrey.

429
00:21:49,224 --> 00:21:52,144
[suspicious music playing]

430
00:21:52,227 --> 00:21:53,937
We saw on the CCTV.

431
00:21:54,021 --> 00:21:57,399
Janine slipped out through the back gate.

432
00:21:57,482 --> 00:21:59,609
What? My granddaughter ran away?

433
00:21:59,693 --> 00:22:01,069
Why was there no guard at the back?

434
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:02,487
[tense music playing]

435
00:22:02,571 --> 00:22:04,823
We need to send my men to look for her.

436
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:06,241
Ah, wait, Dad.

437
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:07,451
Let me do it first.

438
00:22:07,951 --> 00:22:10,454
I feel like I know where she went.

439
00:22:11,496 --> 00:22:12,456
‪[Audrey sighs]

440
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:16,293
[Atoy] Tonet.

441
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:20,005
Deliver that tomorrow.

442
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:21,965
I need your help.

443
00:22:22,507 --> 00:22:24,384
Can you help me…

444
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:27,095
[soft rock music playing]

445
00:22:28,055 --> 00:22:30,098
Looks like you've got a mission, Atoy.

446
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,308
That's right.

447
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:32,601
What's the look you're going for?

448
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:34,352
This.

449
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:39,149
Oh. Ah…

450
00:22:41,526 --> 00:22:42,944
This is easy.

451
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:44,237
Oh, wait.

452
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:46,198
Why are you waiting on the street?

453
00:22:46,281 --> 00:22:47,532
Who are you looking for?

454
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:51,953
[rock music playing]

455
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:53,455
A criminal.

456
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:04,716
[Mongki] What's up, Boss?

457
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,759
You suddenly called.

458
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:07,719
I'm short on shipment.

459
00:23:07,803 --> 00:23:09,096
We need to order new stock.

460
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:10,305
Yes, Boss. What's the hustle?

461
00:23:10,388 --> 00:23:12,307
[Mongki on phone] <i>I'll have some</i>
<i>quality shipment picked up.</i>

462
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:13,683
<i>Maybe just one or two.</i>

463
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:14,935
- You're new here, huh?
- [Emerson stutters]

464
00:23:15,018 --> 00:23:16,311
[Emerson] <i>Atoy, is that really you?</i>

465
00:23:16,394 --> 00:23:17,854
[Red] <i>I know you know</i>
<i>what I'm talking about.</i>

466
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:18,814
You're from the same congregation.

467
00:23:18,897 --> 00:23:19,898
I know your clothing!

468
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:21,108
[scoffs] Nun--

469
00:23:21,191 --> 00:23:22,859
- [quirky sting]
- Why are you picking on a nun?

470
00:23:22,943 --> 00:23:25,237
Why are you meddling?
Do you want me to pinch you, huh?!

471
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:27,072
Oh, what, what? Oh, what?!

472
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:30,200
Son of a thread. They caught on!

473
00:23:30,283 --> 00:23:31,785
UP NEXT

474
00:23:31,868 --> 00:23:35,789
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

475
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:37,999
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪
- [horn honks]

476
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:40,377
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i>
<i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

477
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:43,213
♪ <i>One cut…</i> ♪

478
00:23:43,296 --> 00:23:45,048
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
